## Query

Query services are provided via a GET HTTPS interface that produces JSON objects. The RDAP exchanges uses Mutual TLS for authentication with the OKIX certificates of the DIME and client.

DIMEs provide query services under the `/.well-known/ome/query/` endpoint for interoperable client discovery. See REF.OME.IFACES for implementation details.

### Uniform Resource Identifier {#query-uri}

The DIMEs Issuing certificate contain the base portion of the URI as described in OKIX. Clients obtain the base URI of a given DET by performing the recursive lookup to obtain the Issuing certificate.

Clients construct the full query string by concatenating the base URI from a certificate and the `/.well-known/ome/query/<ipv6>` of the desired DET before performing the HTTPS GET call. 

